(c) The so-called epistolery use es the tenses is the com· monest peculiarity in the use of tenses to be found in the Letters. The writer of the letter imagines ¹himself in the place of the recipient, and therefore uses a tense of past time in speaking of an event which was exactly or approxi- rnately contemporaneous with the'writing of the letter.
